      "id": "intro-0",
      "sectionId": "intro",
      "title": "Intro",
      "body": "The [OCaml](https://www.ocaml.org/) cheat sheet is a one-page reference sheet for the OCaml programming language."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-1",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "hello.ml",
      "body": "%60%60%60ml%0Alet%20()%20%3D%0A%20%20let%20message%20%3D%20%22Hello%2C%20World!%22%20in%0A%20%20Printf.printf%20%22%25s%5Cn%22%20message%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-2",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Compile and Run",
      "body": "```bash\n$ ocamlc -o hello.byte hello.ml\n$ ./hello.byte\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-3",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Build and Run with Dune",
      "body": "```bash\n$ dune build hello.exe\n$ _build/default/hello.exe\n\n# you can also just run\n$ dune exec ./hello.exe\n```\n\nSee the [dune](https://dune.build/) documentation for more info."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-5",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Imports",
      "body": "Install modules with opam\n\n```bash\n$ opam install hex\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-7",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Global Open",
      "body": "```ml\nopen Hex\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-8",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Local%20Open",
      "body": "%60%60%60ml%0AHex.of_string%20%22hex%20string%22%0A%0Alet%20open%20Hex%20in%0A%20%20of_string%20%22to%20hex%22%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-9",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Comments - Line & Block Comments",
      "body": "```ml\n(* A single line comment *)\n\n(* A multi-line comment\n* where we want to explain\n* something complex *)\n\n(* Outer comment\n   (* Nested comment *)\n   End of outer comment *)\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-10",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Documentation Comments",
      "body": "```ml\nval sum : int -> int -> int\n(** [sum x y] returns the sum\n of two integers [x] and [y] *)\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-11",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Predefined Types - Unit",
      "body": "Note: `#` Indicates execution at the toplevel followed by the output\n\n```ml\n# ();; (* equivalent to void in C *)\n- : unit = ()\n```"
    },
    {
