      "title": "Lists",
      "body": "%60%60%60ml%0A%23%20%5B1%3B%202%3B%203%5D%3B%3B%0A-%20%3A%20int%20list%20%3D%20%5B1%3B%202%3B%203%3B%5D%0A%0A%23%20%5B%22a%22%3B%20%22str%22%3B%20%22lst%22%5D%3B%3B%0A-%20%3A%20string%20list%20%3D%20%5B%22a%22%3B%20%22str%22%3B%20%22lst%22%5D%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ALists%20are%20immutable%0A%0A%60%60%60ml%0A%23%20let%20lst%20%3D%20%5B1%3B%202%3B%203%5D%3B%3B%0A-%20%3A%20int%20list%20%3D%20%5B1%3B%202%3B%203%5D%0A%0A%23%20let%20new_lst%20%3D%20%200%20%3A%3A%20lst%3B%3B%20(*%20prepend%20to%20a%20new%20list%20*)%0A-%20%3A%20int%20list%20%3D%20%5B0%3B%201%3B%202%3B%203%5D%0A%0A%23%20new_lst%20%40%20%5B4%3B5%3B6%5D%3B%3B%20(*%20combine%20two%20lists%20*)%0A-%20%3A%20int%20list%20%3D%20%5B0%3B%201%3B%202%3B%203%3B%204%3B%205%3B%206%5D%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-21",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "User-Defined%20Types%20-%20Records",
      "body": "Bundle%20related%20data%0A%0A%60%60%60ml%0Atype%20person%20%3D%20%7B%0A%20%20name%3A%20string%3B%0A%20%20age%3A%20int%0A%7D%0A%0A%23%20let%20zeno%20%3D%20%7Bname%20%3D%20%22Zeno%22%3B%20age%20%3D%2030%7D%3B%3B%0Aval%20zeno%20%3A%20person%20%3D%20%7Bname%20%3D%20%22Zeno%22%3B%20age%20%3D%2030%7D%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-23",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Variants",
      "body": "Several different, but related types\n\n```ml\ntype shape =\n  | Circle of float\n  | Rectangle of float * float\n\n# let my_shape = Circle 5.0;;\n- : shape = Circle 5.\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-25",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Aliases",
      "body": "Provide meaningful name to complex or commonly used types\n\n```ml\ntype point = float * float\n\n# let origin: point = (0.0, 0.0);;\nval origin : point = (0., 0.)\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-27",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Functions - Single parameter",
      "body": "```ml\nlet add_one x =\n  let result = x + 1 in\n  result\n\n# add_one 1;;\n- : int = 2\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-28",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Multiple parameters",
      "body": "```ml\nlet sum x y =\n  let result = x + y in\n  result\n\n# sum 1 2;;\n- : int = 3\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-29",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Tuple%20parameter",
      "body": "%60%60%60ml%0Alet%20str_concat%20(x%2C%20y)%20%3D%0A%20%20x%20%5E%20%22%20%22%20%5E%20y%0A%0A%23%20str_concat%20(%22Hello%22%2C%20%22OCaml%22)%20%3B%3B%0A-%20%3A%20string%20%3D%20%22Hello%20Ocaml%22%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-30",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Recursive Functions - rec keyword",
      "body": "All recusive functions use the rec keyword\n\n```ml\nlet rec factorial n =\n  if n < 1 then 1 else n * factorial (n - 1)\n```\n\nThe above can cause stackoverflow."
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-33",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Tail Recursion",
      "body": "Makes use of a helper function and the acc argument.\n\n```ml\nlet rec factorial_helper n acc =\n  if n = 0 then acc\n  else factorial_helper (n - 1) (n * acc)\n```\n\nNotice the last call is the recursive function.\n\n```ml\nlet factorial n = factorial_helper n 1\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-37",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Chaining - Application Operator",
      "body": "Read from right to left, the first operation is `sum 2 3`\n\n```ml\n(* find log(2 + 3) *)\n# log @@ float_of_int @@ sum 2 3 ;;\n- : float = 1.609...\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-39",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Pipeline",
      "body": "```ml\n(* find log((x + y)!) *)\n# sum 2 3\n  |> factorial\n  |> float_of_int\n  |> log ;;\n- : float = 4.787...\n```\n\n`|>` takes the output of the function and passes it as input to the next function in the pipeline"
    },
    {
