      "sectionId": "s4",
      "title": "If%20Statements%20-%20If%20Statement",
      "body": "%60%60%60ml%0Alet%20is_pos%20x%20%3D%0A%20%20if%20x%20%3E%200%20then%20%22positive%22%20else%20%22negative%22%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s4-42",
      "sectionId": "s4",
      "title": "If%20else%20if",
      "body": "%60%60%60ml%0Alet%20f%20x%20%3D%0A%20%20if%20x%20%3E%203%20then%20%22gt%203%22%0A%20%20else%20if%20x%20%3C%203%20then%20%22lt%203%22%0A%20%20else%20%22eq%203%22%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s4-43",
      "sectionId": "s4",
      "title": "Pattern%20Matching",
      "body": "%60%60%60ml%0Alet%20is_pos%20x%20%3D%0A%20%20match%20x%20%3E%200%20with%0A%20%20%7C%20true%20%20-%3E%20%22positive%22%0A%20%20%7C%20false%20-%3E%20%22negative%22%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s4-44",
      "sectionId": "s4",
      "title": "Loops - For loop",
      "body": "```ml\nfor i = 1 to 5 do\n  print_int i\ndone\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s4-45",
      "sectionId": "s4",
      "title": "While loop",
      "body": "Notice the `ref` is needed to have the while condition eventually become false.\n\n```ml\nlet i = ref 0 in\n  while !i < 5 do\n    print_int !i;\n    i := !i + 1\n  done\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s4-47",
      "sectionId": "s4",
      "title": "Operators - Comparison Operators",
      "body": "```ml\n=         (* equal to *)\n<>        (* not equal to *)\n>         (* greater than *)\n<         (* less than *)\n>=        (* greater than or eq to *)\n<=        (* less than or eq to *)\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s4-48",
      "sectionId": "s4",
      "title": "Arithmatic Operators",
      "body": "```ml\n(* int operator   float operator *)\n+                 +.  (* addition *)\n-                 -.  (* subtraction *)\n*                 *.  (* multiplication *)\n/                 /.  (* division *)\n                  **  (* power *)\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s5-49",
      "sectionId": "s5",
      "title": "List - Searching & Filtering",
      "body": "```ml\n# let lst = [1; 2; 3];;\nval lst : int list = [1; 2; 3]\n\n# List.filter (fun x -> x mod 2 = 0) lst;;\n- : int list = [2]\n\n# List.find (fun x -> x = 4) lst;;\nException: Not_found\n\n# List.sort compare [2; 1; 3];;\n- : int list = [1; 2; 3]\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s5-50",
      "sectionId": "s5",
      "title": "Applying Transformations",
      "body": "```ml\n(* Loop over list and apply fun f *)\nList.iter f lst\n\n(* map a function to each elem *)\n(* Ex. double each element x in lst *)\nList.map (fun x -> x + x) lst\n\n(* Apply an operator between elements *)\n(* Ex. 1 + 2 + 3 *)\nList.fold_left (+) 0 lst\n```"
    },
